      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "VANCOUVER, Wash, Dec. 21.-\nUpon the Inauguration of service\nover the new bridge to Vancouver\nby the Northern Pacific the old\nferry boat crossing the Columbia\nat Kalama, which has been in use\nfor SO years, will be tied up. The\nSeattle Portland trains now cross\ninto Washington but a few miles\nfrom the Portland terminus. The\nold road from Portland to Goble,\nwhere the trains formerly crossed\nthe river will now be used exclu-\nsively for the Astoria trains."
    }
